there's one I've read partially but I haven't found the rest of it the one on
Black Lantern and Snowfire that was published as was that a novel The Power of

44:36.610 --> 44:49.330
Blackness oh okay it was three five novel that's put together three of them ran
in the magazine of fantasy and science fiction and and I guess one in Galaxy and

44:49.330 --> 44:59.530
one in Amazing one thing I saw I wasn't I wasn't It seemed to me, especially as
a teacher of English, I guess, I look for symbolism in some places, a Black

44:59.530 --> 45:09.250
Lantern seemed to me to represent, say, the third world, the oppressed, the
Africans, the Latin Americans, a black man from the streets. I think so. My

45:09.250 --> 45:23.590
original notion in the story was to write a thought, a sort of thought
experiment to set up a story situation that would be a test of primitivism

45:23.590 --> 45:34.750
versus progress. You know, the theme of primitivism is something that we as
teachers of literature are a delight to discover at William Faulkner or

45:34.750 --> 45:49.390
whatever. What I did in the story was to set up the planet Nggongga, which was
settled many thousand years ago by refugees from a wrecked spaceship or fell

45:49.390 --> 46:03.310
back into savagery on a hard world so they developed a very primitive society,
meanwhile the galactic civilization continued to evolve so that when Nggongga is

46:03.310 --> 46:19.430
rediscovered where we have, let's say an ultimately sophisticated technology in
contrast with more or less ultimate primitivism and Black Rated is presented as

46:19.430 --> 46:31.590
a member of the primitive society in conflict with the other society. At that
time, I was still teaching school, so I did the thing as a series of novelettes,

46:31.730 --> 46:42.330
so it's just a way of getting it written and published. It probably lacks unity,
and I feel myself at the middle section of it that's probably better than the

46:42.330 --> 46:50.650
two concluding sections. Did you mean for one of the characters in that story, I
think his name was Toolsmith, did you mean for him to be the same as Ironsmith,

46:50.770 --> 47:02.610
because he does speak for the computer, the machine, more or less… I wondered,
especially the similarity of name, and the way they thought… He's certainly a

47:02.610 --> 47:16.730
representative of the technological culture. Will Snowfire have any symbolic
value, although that's not quite the word? Well, I wanted a romance, a love

47:16.730 --> 47:32.550
interest, and she appealed to me as a sophisticated, civilized person in contact
with a savage on his way up. And I thought that there would be electricity

47:32.550 --> 47:37.290
between them. The name probably is not too successful.

47:42.910 --> 47:46.410
You didn't mean for black and snow, Black Lantern, Snowfire?

